</tr><tr><td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%"><div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini"><ul><li class="nv-view"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Template:E_(mathematical_constant)" title="Template:E (mathematical constant)"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-talk"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Template_talk:E_(mathematical_constant)" title="Template talk:E (mathematical constant)"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-edit"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:E_(mathematical_constant)&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table><p id="mwDQ">The number <b id="mwDg"><span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt9" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwDw">e</span></b> is a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Mathematical_constant" title="Mathematical constant" id="mwEA">mathematical constant</a> that is the base of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Natural_logarithm" title="Natural logarithm" id="mwEQ">natural logarithm</a>: the unique number whose natural logarithm is equal to one. It is approximately equal to <b id="mwEg">2.71828</b>,<sup about="#mwt14" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-1" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-1"}}'><a href="./E_(mathematical_constant)#cite_note-1" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 1;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[1]</span></a></sup> and is the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Limit_of_a_sequence" title="Limit of a sequence" id="mwEw">limit</a> of <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt10" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"(1 + 1/&apos;&apos;n&apos;&apos;)&lt;sup>&apos;&apos;n&apos;&apos;&lt;/sup>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwFA">(1 + 1/<i>n</i>)<sup><i>n</i></sup></span> as <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt11" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"n"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwFQ">n</span> approaches <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Infinity" title="Infinity" id="mwFg">infinity</a>, an expression that arises in the study of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Compound_interest" title="Compound interest" id="mwFw">compound interest</a>. It can also be calculated as the sum of the infinite <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Series_(mathematics)" title="Series (mathematics)" id="mwGA">series</a><sup about="#mwt16" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-2" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-2"}}'><a href="./E_(mathematical_constant)#cite_note-2" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 2;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[2]</span></a></sup></p>

<dl id="mwGQ"><dd id="mwGg"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt261" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"e =  \\displaystyle\\sum\\limits_{n = 0}^{ \\infty} \\dfrac{1}{n!} = \\frac{1}{1} + \\frac{1}{1} + \\frac{1}{1\\cdot 2} + \\frac{1}{1\\cdot 2\\cdot 3} + \\cdots"}}' id="mwGw"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle e=\displaystyle \sum \limits _{n=0}^{\infty }{\dfrac {1}{n!}}={\frac {1}{1}}+{\frac {1}{1}}+{\frac {1}{1\cdot 2}}+{\frac {1}{1\cdot 2\cdot 3}}+\cdots }">
