      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle n=\lfloor L/e\rfloor ,\,\,{\text{or }}\,\,\lfloor L/e\rfloor +1.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8087ce21ded6b0ea604317104eb0e48de89cf7e4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:26.167ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle n=\lfloor L/e\rfloor ,\,\,{\text{or }}\,\,\lfloor L/e\rfloor +1.}"/></span><span about="#mwt441">
</span></dd></dl>
<p id="mw1A">The stated result follows because the maximum value of <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt443" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"x^{-1}\\ln x"}}' id="mw1Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle x^{-1}\ln x}">
