      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 1/x}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a55fefc6f37f48a9b4414b09ad3b17dfa739d9e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:3.655ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle 1/x}"/></span><span about="#mwt449">
</span>, so that essentially the same optimal division appears in optimal planning problems like the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Secretary_problem" title="Secretary problem" id="mw3A">secretary problem</a>.</p>

</section><section data-mw-section-id="7" id="mw3Q"><h3 id="Asymptotics">Asymptotics</h3>
<p id="mw3g">The number <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt135" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw3w">e</span> occurs naturally in connection with many problems involving <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Asymptotics" title="Asymptotics" id="mw4A" class="mw-redirect">asymptotics</a>. An example is <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Stirling's_formula" title="Stirling's formula" id="mw4Q" class="mw-redirect">Stirling's formula</a> for the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Asymptotic_analysis" title="Asymptotic analysis" id="mw4g">asymptotics</a> of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Factorial_function" title="Factorial function" id="mw4w" class="mw-redirect">factorial function</a>, in which both the numbers <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt136" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw5A">e</span> and <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Pi" title="Pi" id="mw5Q"><span class="texhtml " about="#mwt137" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"pi","href":"./Template:Pi"},"params":{},"i":0}}]}' id="mw5g">π</span></a> enter:</p>
<dl id="mw5w"><dd id="mw6A"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt451" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"n! \\sim \\sqrt{2\\pi n}\\, \\left(\\frac{n}{e}\\right)^n."}}' id="mw6Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle n!\sim {\sqrt {2\pi n}}\,\left({\frac {n}{e}}\right)^{n}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo>!</mo>
        <mo>∼<!-- ∼ --></mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mn>2</mn>
            <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msup>
          <mrow>
            <mo>(</mo>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mi>n</mi>
                <mi>e</mi>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle n!\sim {\sqrt {2\pi n}}\,\left({\frac {n}{e}}\right)^{n}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/25e4c057afab2d900ef7a4513149795a866228e0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:18.224ex; height:4.843ex;" alt="n!\sim {\sqrt {2\pi n}}\,\left({\frac {n}{e}}\right)^{n}."/></span><span about="#mwt451">
</span></dd></dl>
<p id="mw6g">As a consequence,</p>
<dl id="mw6w"><dd id="mw7A"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt453" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"e = \\lim_{n\\to\\infty} \\frac{n}{\\sqrt[n]{n!}} ."}}' id="mw7Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle e=\lim _{n\to \infty }{\frac {n}{\sqrt[{n}]{n!}}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>e</mi>
