</span></dd></dl>

</section><section data-mw-section-id="8" id="mw7g"><h3 id="Standard_normal_distribution">Standard normal distribution</h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" about="#mwt140" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"main article","href":"./Template:Main_article"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Normal distribution"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw7w">Main article: <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Normal_distribution" title="Normal distribution">Normal distribution</a></div>

<p id="mw8A">The normal distribution with zero mean and unit standard deviation is known as the <i id="mw8Q">standard normal distribution</i>, given by the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Probability_density_function" title="Probability density function" id="mw8g">probability density function</a></p>

<dl id="mw8w"><dd id="mw9A"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt455" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\phi(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2\\pi}}\\, e^{- \\frac{\\scriptscriptstyle 1}{\\scriptscriptstyle 2} x^2}."}}' id="mw9Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \phi (x)={\frac {1}{\sqrt {2\pi }}}\,e^{-{\frac {\scriptscriptstyle 1}{\scriptscriptstyle 2}}x^{2}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>ϕ<!-- ϕ --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <msqrt>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
            </msqrt>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msup>
          <mi>e</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="2">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mstyle>
                <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="2">
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mstyle>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \phi (x)={\frac {1}{\sqrt {2\pi }}}\,e^{-{\frac {\scriptscriptstyle 1}{\scriptscriptstyle 2}}x^{2}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5fc450d286e3eb52a317041254cffcaac30ee690" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.838ex; width:19.793ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="\phi (x)={\frac {1}{\sqrt {2\pi }}}\,e^{-{\frac {\scriptscriptstyle 1}{\scriptscriptstyle 2}}x^{2}}."/></span><span about="#mwt455">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mw9g">The constraint of unit variance (and thus also unit standard deviation) results in the <span class="sfrac nowrap" style="display:inline-block; vertical-align:-0.5em; font-size:85%; text-align:center;" about="#mwt144" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"frac2","href":"./Template:Frac2"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"1"},"2":{"wt":"2"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw9w"><span style="display:block; line-height:1em; margin:0 0.1em;">1</span><span class="visualhide">/</span><span style="display:block; line-height:1em; margin:0 0.1em; border-top:1px solid;">2</span></span> in the exponent, and the constraint of unit total area under the curve <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt145" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;ϕ&apos;&apos;(&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw-A"><i>ϕ</i>(<i>x</i>)</span> results in the factor <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt457" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\textstyle 1/\\sqrt{2\\pi}"}}' id="mw-Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>/</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msqrt>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
            </msqrt>
          </mrow>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6bc8e3e4df369ae48dea75e5d9ce018177064a69" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.755ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}"/></span><span about="#mwt457">
</span>.<sup id="mw-g"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Gaussian_integral" title="Gaussian integral" id="mw-w">[proof]</a></sup>  This function is symmetric around <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt146" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos; = 0"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw_A"><i>x</i> = 0</span>, where it attains its maximum value <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt459" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\textstyle 1/\\sqrt{2\\pi}"}}' id="mw_Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>/</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msqrt>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>π<!-- π --></mi>
            </msqrt>
          </mrow>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6bc8e3e4df369ae48dea75e5d9ce018177064a69" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.755ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \textstyle 1/{\sqrt {2\pi }}}"/></span><span about="#mwt459">
</span>, and has <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Inflection_point" title="Inflection point" id="mw_g">inflection points</a> at <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt147" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos; = ±1"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw_w"><i>x</i> = ±1</span>.</p>

</section></section><section data-mw-section-id="9" id="mwAQA"><h2 id="In_calculus">In calculus</h2>

<figure class="mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:Image/Thumb" id="mwAQE"><a href="./File:Exp_derivative_at_0.svg" id="mwAQI"><img resource="./File:Exp_derivative_at_0.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Exp_derivative_at_0.svg/220px-Exp_derivative_at_0.svg.png" data-file-width="255" data-file-height="255" data-file-type="drawing" height="220" width="220" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Exp_derivative_at_0.svg/440px-Exp_derivative_at_0.svg.png 2x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Exp_derivative_at_0.svg/330px-Exp_derivative_at_0.svg.png 1.5x" id="mwAQM"/></a><figcaption id="mwAQQ">The graphs of the functions <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt148" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos; ↦ &apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos;{{sup|&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;}}"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQU"><i>x</i> ↦ <i>a</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> are shown for <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt149" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos; = 2"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQY"><i>a</i> = 2</span> (dotted), <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt150" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos; = &apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQc"><i>a</i> = <i>e</i></span> (blue), and <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt151" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos; = 4"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQg"><i>a</i> = 4</span> (dashed). They all pass through the point <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt152" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"(0,1)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQk">(0,1)</span>, but the red line (which has slope <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt153" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"1"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQo">1</span>) is tangent to only <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt154" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;{{sup|&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;}}"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAQs"><i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> there.</figcaption></figure>

<figure class="mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:Image/Thumb" id="mwAQw"><a href="./File:Ln+e.svg" id="mwAQ0"><img resource="./File:Ln+e.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Ln%2Be.svg/220px-Ln%2Be.svg.png" data-file-width="400" data-file-height="250" data-file-type="drawing" height="138" width="220" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Ln%2Be.svg/440px-Ln%2Be.svg.png 2x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Ln%2Be.svg/330px-Ln%2Be.svg.png 1.5x" id="mwAQ4"/></a><figcaption id="mwAQ8">The value of the natural log function for argument <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt155" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwARA">e</span>, i.e. <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt156" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"ln(&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwARE">ln(<i>e</i>)</span>, equals <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt157" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"1."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwARI">1.</span></figcaption></figure>

<p id="mwARM">The principal motivation for introducing the number <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt159" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwARQ">e</span>, particularly in <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Calculus" title="Calculus" id="mwARU">calculus</a>, is to perform <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Derivative_(mathematics)" title="Derivative (mathematics)" id="mwARY" class="mw-redirect">differential</a> and <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Integral_calculus" title="Integral calculus" id="mwARc" class="mw-redirect">integral calculus</a> with <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Exponential_function" title="Exponential function" id="mwARg">exponential functions</a> and <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Logarithm" title="Logarithm" id="mwARk">logarithms</a>.<sup about="#mwt649" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-16" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-16"}}'><a href="./E_(mathematical_constant)#cite_note-16" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 16;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[16]</span></a></sup> A general exponential <span class="nowrap" about="#mwt161" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"nowrap","href":"./Template:Nowrap"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"function {{math|&apos;&apos;y&apos;&apos; {{=}} &apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos;&lt;sup>&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;&lt;/sup>}}"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwARo">function <span class="texhtml "><i>y</i> = <i>a</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span></span> has a derivative, given by a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Limit_of_a_function" title="Limit of a function" id="mwARs">limit</a>:</p>

<dl id="mwARw"><dd id="mwAR0"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt464" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{"display":"inline"},"body":{"extsrc":"\\begin{align}\n\\frac{d}{dx}a^x &amp;=\\lim_{h\\to 0}\\frac{a^{x+h}-a^x}{h}=\\lim_{h\\to 0}\\frac{a^{x}a^{h}-a^x}{h} \\\\\n&amp;=a^x\\cdot \\left(\\lim_{h\\to 0}\\frac{a^h-1}{h}\\right).\n\\end{align}"}}' id="mwAR4"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\textstyle {\begin{aligned}{\frac {d}{dx}}a^{x}&amp;=\lim _{h\to 0}{\frac {a^{x+h}-a^{x}}{h}}=\lim _{h\to 0}{\frac {a^{x}a^{h}-a^{x}}{h}}\\&amp;=a^{x}\cdot \left(\lim _{h\to 0}{\frac {a^{h}-1}{h}}\right).\end{aligned}}}">
