</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwASg">Consequently, the exponential function with base <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt169" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwASk">e</span> is particularly suited to doing calculus. <span class="nowrap" about="#mwt170" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"nowrap","href":"./Template:Nowrap"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Choosing {{mvar|e}},"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwASo">Choosing <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>,</span> as opposed to some other number, as the base of the exponential function makes calculations involving the derivative much simpler.</p>

<p id="mwASs">Another motivation comes from considering the derivative of the base-<span class="texhtml " about="#mwt172" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwASw"><i>a</i></span> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Logarithm" title="Logarithm" id="mwAS0">logarithm</a>,<sup about="#mwt177" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-17" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-17"}}'><a href="./E_(mathematical_constant)#cite_note-17" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 17;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[17]</span></a></sup> i.e., of <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt173" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"log&lt;sub>&apos;&apos;a&apos;&apos;&lt;/sub> &apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAS4">log<sub><i>a</i></sub> <i>x</i></span> for<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAS8"> </span><span class="texhtml " about="#mwt174" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"x > 0"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwATA">x > 0</span>:</p>

<dl id="mwATE"><dd id="mwATI"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt468" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{"display":"inline"},"body":{"extsrc":"\\begin{align}\n\\frac{d}{dx}\\log_a x &amp;= \\lim_{h\\to 0}\\frac{\\log_a(x+h)-\\log_a(x)}{h} \\\\\n&amp;=\\lim_{h\\to 0}\\frac{\\log_a(1+h/x)}{x\\cdot h/x} \\\\\n&amp;=\\frac{1}{x}\\log_a\\left(\\lim_{u\\to 0}(1+u)^{1/u}\\right) \\\\\n&amp;=\\frac{1}{x}\\log_a e,\n\\end{align}"}}' id="mwATM"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\textstyle {\begin{aligned}{\frac {d}{dx}}\log _{a}x&amp;=\lim _{h\to 0}{\frac {\log _{a}(x+h)-\log _{a}(x)}{h}}\\&amp;=\lim _{h\to 0}{\frac {\log _{a}(1+h/x)}{x\cdot h/x}}\\&amp;={\frac {1}{x}}\log _{a}\left(\lim _{u\to 0}(1+u)^{1/u}\right)\\&amp;={\frac {1}{x}}\log _{a}e,\end{aligned}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
