    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \tau =f(t)/f'(t)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7a3a299ec909f0e676e3ac4b0dc9db280f4126db" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:14.044ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \tau =f(t)/f'(t)}"/></span><span about="#mwt486">
</span> is a constant, sometimes called the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Time_constant" title="Time constant" id="mwAYA">time constant</a> (it is the reciprocal of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Exponential_growth" title="Exponential growth" id="mwAYE">exponential growth constant</a> or <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Exponential_decay" title="Exponential decay" id="mwAYI">decay constant</a>).  The time constant is the time it takes for the exponential function to increase by a factor of <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt213" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAYM"><i>e</i></span>: <span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt488" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"f(t+\\tau) = e f(t)"}}' id="mwAYQ"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle f(t+\tau )=ef(t)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>f</mi>
