            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle e^{x}=1+{x \over 1!}+{x^{2} \over 2!}+{x^{3} \over 3!}+\cdots =\sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {x^{n}}{n!}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/189e40af63e698de00f0b071c7f57bb587264c49" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:39.912ex; height:6.843ex;" alt="e^{x}=1+{x \over 1!}+{x^{2} \over 2!}+{x^{3} \over 3!}+\cdots =\sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {x^{n}}{n!}}"/></span><span about="#mwt555">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwAf4">Because this series keeps many important properties for <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt282" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;&lt;sup>&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;&lt;/sup>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAf8"><i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> even when <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt283" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAgA"><i>x</i></span> is <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Complex_number" title="Complex number" id="mwAgE">complex</a>, it is commonly used to extend the definition of <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt284" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;&lt;sup>&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;&lt;/sup>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAgI"><i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> to the complex numbers. This, with the Taylor series for <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Trigonometric_functions" title="Trigonometric functions" id="mwAgM"><span class="texhtml " about="#mwt285" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"sin"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAgQ">sin</span> and <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt286" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"cos &apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAgU">cos <i>x</i></span></a>, allows one to derive <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Euler's_formula" title="Euler's formula" id="mwAgY">Euler's formula</a>:</p>

<dl id="mwAgc"><dd id="mwAgg"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt557" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"e^{ix} = \\cos x + i\\sin x ,"}}' id="mwAgk"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle e^{ix}=\cos x+i\sin x,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msup>
          <mi>e</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>cos</mi>
        <mo>⁡<!-- ⁡ --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
