</span></dd></dl>

</section></section><section data-mw-section-id="18" id="mwAjM"><h2 id="Representations">Representations</h2>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" about="#mwt300" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Main article","href":"./Template:Main_article"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"List of representations of e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAjQ">Main article: <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./List_of_representations_of_e" title="List of representations of e">List of representations of e</a></div>

<p id="mwAjU">The number <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;" about="#mwt301" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"mvar","href":"./Template:Mvar"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"e"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAjY">e</span> can be represented as a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Real_number" title="Real number" id="mwAjc">real number</a> in a variety of ways: as an <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Infinite_series" title="Infinite series" id="mwAjg" class="mw-redirect">infinite series</a>, an <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Infinite_product" title="Infinite product" id="mwAjk">infinite product</a>, a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Continued_fraction" title="Continued fraction" id="mwAjo">continued fraction</a>, or a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Limit_of_a_sequence" title="Limit of a sequence" id="mwAjs">limit of a sequence</a>. The chief among these representations, particularly in introductory <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Calculus" title="Calculus" id="mwAjw">calculus</a> courses is the limit</p>
<dl id="mwAj0"><dd id="mwAj4"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt577" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\left(1+\\frac{1}{n}\\right)^n,"}}' id="mwAj8"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \lim _{n\to \infty }\left(1+{\frac {1}{n}}\right)^{n},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <munder>
          <mo movablelimits="true" form="prefix">lim</mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">→<!-- → --></mo>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">∞<!-- ∞ --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </munder>
        <msup>
          <mrow>
            <mo>(</mo>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mfrac>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                  <mi>n</mi>
                </mfrac>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mo>)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lim _{n\to \infty }\left(1+{\frac {1}{n}}\right)^{n},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6abb8f4094bafd4757b3e350336fbc66a4b67675" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:16.18ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="\lim _{n\to \infty }\left(1+{\frac {1}{n}}\right)^{n},"/></span><span about="#mwt577">
</span></dd></dl>
<p id="mwAkA">given above, as well as the series</p>
<dl id="mwAkE"><dd id="mwAkI"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt579" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"e=\\sum_{n=0}^\\infty \\frac{1}{n!}"}}' id="mwAkM"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle e=\sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {1}{n!}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>∑<!-- ∑ --></mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>=</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="normal">∞<!-- ∞ --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo>!</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle e=\sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {1}{n!}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2019b8b95ec12a0b8cdc76c92583bc574d37a863" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:10.802ex; height:6.843ex;" alt="e=\sum _{n=0}^{\infty }{\frac {1}{n!}}"/></span><span about="#mwt579">
</span></dd></dl>
<p id="mwAkQ">given by evaluating the above <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Power_series" title="Power series" id="mwAkU">power series</a> for <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt304" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;e&apos;&apos;&lt;sup>&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos;&lt;/sup>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAkY"><i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> at <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt305" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;x&apos;&apos; {{=}} 1"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAkc"><i>x</i> = 1</span>.</p>

<p id="mwAkg">Less common is the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Continued_fraction" title="Continued fraction" id="mwAkk">continued fraction</a> <span about="#mwt306" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"OEIS","href":"./Template:OEIS"},"params":{"id":{"wt":"A003417"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAko">(sequence </span><span class="nowrap" about="#mwt306"><a rel="mw:WikiLink/Interwiki" href="//oeis.org/A003417" title="oeis:A003417">A003417</a></span><span about="#mwt306"> in the </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./On-Line_Encyclopedia_of_Integer_Sequences" title="On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences" about="#mwt306">OEIS</a><span about="#mwt306">)</span>.</p>
<!--move to history section or say <ref&#x3E;[[Leonhard Euler|Euler]] was the first showed that {{mvar|e}} can be represented as a continued fraction.</ref&#x3E;-->

<dl id="mwAks"><dd id="mwAkw"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt581" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\ne = [2;1,2,1,1,4,1,1,6,1,...,1,2n,1,...],\n"}}' id="mwAk0"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle e=[2;1,2,1,1,4,1,1,6,1,...,1,2n,1,...],}">
  <semantics>
